#2671
Inside the house~
An odd place, to be sure. This must be the home of the man who takes care of
the clock tower, because it is obvious whoever lives here is obsessed with
time. Dozens of clocks of various shapes and sizes lie about here, Cukoo
clocks adorn the walls, and three rather impressive grandfather clocks stand
in the middle of each of the three walls to the south, east and west. Every
table in the house has a clock on it, if not more than one.
